Note that `getPort(size_t)` works fine when `symName` was supplied, as shown on first case but crashes otherwise.

## Analysis

`getPorts()` constructs `firrtl::PortInfo` with `getPortSymbolAttr(i)` directly.
```cpp
static SmallVector<PortInfo> getPortImpl(FModuleLike module) {
  SmallVector<PortInfo> results;
  for (unsigned i = 0, e = module.getNumPorts(); i < e; ++i) {
    results.push_back({module.getPortNameAttr(i), module.getPortType(i),
                       module.getPortDirection(i), module.getPortSymbolAttr(i),
                       module.getPortLocation(i),
                       AnnotationSet::forPort(module, i)});
  }
  return results;
}

SmallVector<PortInfo> FModuleOp::getPorts() { return ::getPortImpl(*this); }

// ...
```

while `getPort(size_t)` constructs `hw::PortInfo` with `NamedAttribute`. Whenever `getPortSymbolAttr(idx)` is null, this will trigger assertion.
```cpp
static hw::PortInfo getPortImpl(FModuleLike module, size_t idx) {
  return {{module.getPortNameAttr(idx), module.getPortType(idx),
           dirFtoH(module.getPortDirection(idx))},
          idx,
          DictionaryAttr::get(
              module.getContext(),
              ArrayRef<mlir::NamedAttribute>{NamedAttribute{
                  StringAttr::get(module.getContext(),
                                  hw::HWModuleLike::getPortSymbolAttrName()),
                  module.getPortSymbolAttr(idx)}}),
          module.getPortLocation(idx)};
}

::circt::hw::PortInfo FModuleOp::getPort(size_t idx) {
  return ::getPortImpl(*this, idx);
}

// ...
```

This code was originated from https://github.com/llvm/circt/commit/8722a98a7b0464d2c95498c6e4a68e7e98e0e70d and as of 12/02/25 the `main` branch remains unchanged. (https://github.com/llvm/circt/blame/main/lib/Dialect/FIRRTL/FIRRTLOps.cpp)

# Reason this issue should be fixed

Even though it's a small issue, it's easy to trip over for unexperienced developers.

- One API silently assumes that a symbol must exist, without documenting that requirement.
- As a result, this result can surprise newcomers.

# Possible workarounds

1. **Supply the optional `symName` or `hw::InnerSymAttr` when constructing `PortInfo`.**

```cpp
    StringType portType = StringType::get(context);
    StringAttr nameAttr = StringAttr::get(context, "name");
    PortInfo nameOut(nameAttr, portType, Direction::Out, nameAttr);
```

2.  **Use `getPorts()` and index access instead.** (This returns `firrtl::PortInfo`)

```cpp
generated.getPorts()[2]
```

